We consume around 5 grams of microplastics every week, that’s the size of a credit card.

They’re in our bottled water, plastic tea bags, food packaging, salt, and even the air we breathe.

Microplastics have been found in human blood, lungs, breast milk, and 100% of placentas tested in a recent study.

They quietly build up, disrupting hormones, triggering inflammation, and increasing long-term health risks.

And most of it comes from things we use every day, without even thinking.
Your chai dip? Might be plastic. That meal prep box? Lined with it.

But the good news? Small swaps make a big difference, loose leaf tea, glass jars, steel bottles, and a little more awareness.

In this episode of #SustainableTeaWithShreya, India’s biggest sustainability podcast, host @shreyaghodawat sits down with Ayurvedic health coach @dimplejangdaofficial to break down where microplastics are hiding, how they harm us, and how ancient wisdom meets modern solutions in protecting our bodies and the planet.

Catch the full episode on YouTube now!

(plastic pollution, healthy lifestyle, sustainability, stws, climate change)

#microplastics #health #plasticfree #ecofriendly #zerowaste #lifestyle

Do you think constantly praising a mother’s ‘sacrifice’ stops them from demanding real support? Share your thoughts in the comments!🤔

The truth is, society rarely asks why so much parenting or caregiving falls on mothers. Instead, we celebrate how well they cope. But coping isn’t the goal right? Balance is.

When fathers share the load, they’re often praised for “stepping up.” But isn’t parenting a shared responsibility? Helping isn’t heroic, it’s just doing your part. Maybe it’s time we stop romanticizing burnout and start valuing equal care, shall we?

#GeneliaDsouza #Motherhood #Parenting

latestPosts.caption:
Did you know your body goes into damage-control mode every time you eat meat?
 
Consuming animal meat puts your system in an acidic state, and your body, always trying to maintain balance, fights back.

It borrows minerals like calcium, magnesium, and phosphorus from your bones to neutralize the acidity.
 
But these minerals don’t disappear, they pass through your bloodstream.
And when there’s excess calcium floating around, it doesn’t exit quietly…
It sticks to your arteries. Because calcium is positively charged and arteries are negatively charged.
 
The result leads to a major cause of artery blockages that goes beyond just cholesterol.

Most people don’t know this, but your daily food choices could be shaping your future health in ways you never imagined. And yes, this link between acidity and arterial health has science behind it.

In the latest episode of #SustainableTeaWithShreya, India’s biggest sustainability podcast, @shreyaghodawat dives into this topic with functional medicine expert @nutritionist_vaibhav.

Catch the full episode on YouTube now! (link in bio)

(plantbased diet, healthy living, heart attack, arteries)

#meatfree #dairyfree #health #plantbased #vegan #diet #stws #calcium #hearthealth #arteries

Every morning, you brush your teeth, wash your face, sip your coffee, head to the gym… and unknowingly invite plastic into your body. 🧴☕👕 

From the toothpaste tube to your protein shake, microplastics are sneaking into your daily habits, tiny particles that can disrupt your hormones, gut health, and long-term well-being. But here’s the good news: you don’t need to do it perfectly to make a difference. ✨

Switching to a bamboo toothbrush, a bar of soap, or glass containers might seem small, but these choices stack up. 🌿 

Every swap is a vote for your health and a cleaner planet. It’s not about perfection, it’s about progress. This Plastic-Free July, let’s choose better, not just for the Earth, but for ourselves too. ❤️

Because when your daily routine stops harming you and the world around you? That’s self-care.

(Plastic-free July, plastic waste, environment, nature, sustainability, biodegradable)

#PlasticFreeJuly #planet #plasticpollution #planet #earth #greenchoices #reducewaste

The future of wellness might look a lot like your Grandma’s kitchen.🌿

@nutritionist_vaibhav walked away from the corporate grind to build something that felt aligned and grounded. That “something” became @inyouwellness, a wellness brand rooted in ancient wisdom, gut-friendly foods, and the power of slowing down.

In this heartfelt conversation, he opens up about his healing journey, how our gut and mind are more connected than we think, and why the answers we’re searching for are already inside us.

If you’re on a path to better eating, better living, or even building something of your own, this one’s for you. Because wellness isn’t a product. It’s a practice. And it starts with tuning in.

In this episode of #SustainableTeaWithShreya, India’s biggest sustainability podcast, @shreyaghodawat sits with @nutritionist_vaibhav for a conversation on food, purpose, and building a brand that begins from the inside out. They talk about fermentation, Indian food traditions, and how we’ve moved so far from the rhythms of our bodies.

It’s honest, hopeful, and full of reminders to come back home, to our health, to our roots, and to the joy of building a life that feels good from within.

Catch the full episode on YouTube now (link in bio)

latestPosts.caption:
Here’s how to stop sipping microplastics with your morning tea.

Sounds dramatic, but it’s disturbingly normal.
Most commercial tea bags are sealed with plastic. And when they’re steeped in hot water, they release billions of microplastic particles into your cup. Not just once. Every single time.

That comforting ritual? It’s quietly adding plastic to your body before your day even begins.

And the worst part is, no one tells you this.
No label. No warning. No awareness.

But there’s a shift brewing.

More brands are moving away from petroleum-based plastic sealing and offering plantbased bags, biodegradable wraps, and cleaner choices, so your chai can be warming, not worrying.

Some of the plastic-free brands I’ve come across include:
🌿 Woolah @be_woolah 
🫖 Dancing Leaf @dancingleafteas 
🌱 Organic India @organicindiaofficial 
🍃 Cambridge Tea Party @cambridgeteapartyofficial 

In a world full of hidden toxins and silent trade-offs, sometimes the most radical thing you can do is sip with awareness.

Which one will you choose today?

#sustainability #microplastics #tea #plasticfree #ecofriendlyliving

We living on borrowed resources. 

As of today, we’ve exhausted the Earth’s natural supply for the year 2025. 🌏

The way we produce, consume, and waste is our planet of its ability to recover, year after year.

1/3rd of all food is wasted before it even reaches a plate.
Fast fashion turns garments into landfill within weeks.
Animal agriculture and meat-heavy diets continue to fuel a system that drains water, land, and climate stability;
Costing us clean air, water, and entire ecosystems. 

But it doesn’t have to stay this way.

Eating plantbased, wasting less, and choosing slower, circular consumption are the solution and our tools for transition. 

If we do this consistently, we can push Earth Overshoot Day back and exit ecological debt entirely by 2050.

If we don’t, we’re defaulting our own future. So how are you resetting the calendar?

Tell us in the comments! 👇

(Earth Overshoot Day, environment, planet, nature, sustainability)

#EarthOvershootDay #overconsumption #consumerism #earth #planet #ecosystem #climatechange

You are what you eat, and more importantly, how you feel is directly linked to what’s on your plate. Most of us focus on calories or macros, but forget the trillions of microbes living inside our gut.
 
They’re not just digesting our food,  they’re influencing our hormones, our skin, our energy levels, and even our thoughts. When you feed your gut right, you think clearer, feel lighter, and live better.

But if you constantly eat processed, animal-heavy, low-fibre foods, your gut doesn’t thrive, and neither do you.

That ‘gut feeling’ we talk about? It’s real. And it’s shaped by what we choose, one bite at a time.

The science is simple: eat plants, feel better. Whole, unprocessed, plantbased foods give your body what it needs to protect, heal, and balance itself✨.

In this episode of #SustainableTeaWithShreya, India’s biggest sustainability podcast, @ShreyaGhodawat explores this in-depth with wellness coach and integrative nutritionist @neharanglani_ 

(healthy eating, nutrition, lifestyle, gut health, plantbased, mental health)

You called me home.🌍

Walked barefoot on my soil, drank from my rivers 💧, and dreamed beneath my skies.

But somewhere along the way, you traded care for convenience.

Now, I wear your waste like a second skin, bags, bottles, and broken promises.

You toss what you no longer need, but I never stop carrying it.

Every plastic scrap whispers a truth: you’re not just littering streets🚯, you’re littering me.

I’m not infinite. I’m not immune.

Treat me like trash, and that’s all I’ll become.

But if you still believe in me, start acting like I’m worth saving.💚

(plastic waste, environment, climate change, pollution, planet)

#earth #nature #environment #plasticpollution #climateaction

Your glow-up could start in the kitchen, not your vanity!

Protein powers your body’s repair system, fuels your cells, and produces collagen, the magic behind glowing skin, healthy hair, and strong nails. ✨

But here's what we miss: you don’t need meat or whey to meet your protein goals.

Nature already gave us a rich menu: lentils, tofu, tempeh, chickpeas, peas, seeds, nuts, and even greens like spinach and moringa.

And when you eat protein in your meals, instead of only depending on powders, it nourishes you from the inside out. 🌿 Think of it as skincare that starts in your kitchen.

In the latest episode of #SustainableTeaWithShreya, India’s biggest sustainability podcast, @shreyaghodawat sat down with the brilliant @drjaishreesharad to talk about holistic skincare, protein-powered diets, plantbased nutrition, and how your daily plate can keep you young, glowing, and grounded.

Catch the full episode on YouTube now!

(skin care, collagen, plantbased protein, healthy eating, nutrition, self care)

#nutrition #healthylifestyle #collagen #plantbased #protein #vegan #skincare

It’s never just a bottle. Or just a bag.
It’s a choice. One that shapes the world we live in.

The average person unknowingly consumes about a credit card’s worth of plastic every week.

From your blood to your lungs to your unborn child’s placenta, microplastics are everywhere. And still, we keep sipping from plastic bottles and wrapping food in toxins.

Meanwhile, marine animals choke on our convenience.
Over 1 million of them die each year, just so we can avoid carrying a cloth bag.

But small swaps aren’t small. They’re daily declarations that say we choose better, for our body, our future, and this planet.

Start with a bottle. A bag. A better habit. And then keep going. 🌱
